.AVIATION...
(12Z TAFS)
Issued at 357 AM PST Wed Nov 27 2024

Light sporadic showers are lingering around the Monterey Bay but
will exit into the late morning. High clouds continue to erode into
the morning, with some pockets of fog in the North Bay dissipating
in the mid morning. Expect mostly light winds through the TAF period
as well as widespread VFR this afternoon and into the night.


Vicinity of SFO...VFR through the TAF period. High clouds reduce
through the day. Light winds linger into the late morning with
moderate northwest winds building for the afternoon. Expect winds to
become light again in the late night.

SFO Bridge Approach...Similar to SFO.

Monterey Bay Terminals...Shower activity lingers into the late
morning. Expect light winds through the TAF period with VFR
conditions.


&&

.MARINE...
(Today through Monday)
Issued at 357 AM PST Wed Nov 27 2024

Lingering light showers are moving across the southern waters and
look to exit in the late morning. Expect light to moderate
northerly winds over the coastal waters through the weekend. A
long period southerly swell will continue to fill in over the
waters tonight and continue into Thursday night.

&&

